This paper deals with modeling and analyzing vehicular networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MA) or statistics (cs.ST). The use of point processes and interference analysis could also fall under signal processing (cs.SI) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with system-level analysis and optimization, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
